#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Pre-1.0 stub. The XLibre swap is now part of install.sh's regular
# pipeline — re-running install.sh --apply gives you the full target
# state (bspwm session + picom v13 + XLibre) from any starting point.
# No separate migration step exists yet.
#
# Once the project starts cutting 1.0+ tags we'll add real upgrade
# migrations (e.g. picom-ftlabs-git → picom for users coming from
# pre-1.0 installs) and this script will get a body.
#
# To revert FROM xlibre back to xorg-server today, do it manually:
#   sudo pacman -S xorg-server xorg-server-common xf86-input-libinput
# Pacman's provides/conflicts logic will swap the xlibre packages out.

cat <<'EOF'
nw-omarchy-xlibre-migrate: no-op until 1.0.

The XLibre swap is part of the install pipeline. Run:

    ./install.sh --apply

from $NW_OMARCHY_PATH (default ~/.local/share/nw-omarchy) to reach
the latest target state — including XLibre — from any starting point.

Manual revert recipe (if you need to drop back to xorg-server):

    sudo pacman -S xorg-server xorg-server-common xf86-input-libinput

See docs/xlibre.md for the full story.
EOF
